  "body": "Improvements\r\n  - Refactored update endpoints - Both beta and stable channels now use a unified GitHub Pages structure (update/beta-dev/latest.json and update/stable/latest.json) for more reliable auto-updates\r\n  - Automatic update channel detection - The app now automatically selects the correct update channel (beta-dev / stable) based on the version string, instead of relying on build mode\r\n  - Stable updater manifest auto-publishing - The production release workflow now automatically publishes the updater manifest to GitHub Pages after each stable release\r\n  - Version consistency validation - Added a check in the release workflow to ensure the pushed git tag matches the version in package.json and Cargo.toml\r\n  - Improved beta version retrieval - Enhanced the logic for determining the next beta version number for more accurate tagging\r\n\r\n  Build & Packaging\r\n  - Explicit bundle targets - Specified exact package formats per platform:\r\n    - macOS: .dmg, .app\r\n    - Linux: .AppImage, .deb, .rpm\r\n    - Windows: .nsis\r\n  - Concurrency control - Added concurrency group to the stable release workflow to prevent duplicate releases\n"
